01:25:06.620 --> 01:25:08.940
What I've told you here
with the projection

01:25:08.940 --> 01:25:12.710
of the electric
field, this is not

01:25:12.710 --> 01:25:17.610
100% rigorous for the
quasi-probabilities Q.

01:25:17.610 --> 01:25:19.930
Due to the non-commutativity
of operators,

01:25:19.930 --> 01:25:24.850
when we generalize phase
space function into quantum

01:25:24.850 --> 01:25:28.730
mechanics, we can order
operators in a symmetric way,

01:25:28.730 --> 01:25:31.000
in a normal way, in
an anti- normal way.

01:25:31.000 --> 01:25:33.770
And therefore, there are three
different quasi-probabilities.

01:25:33.770 --> 01:25:37.400
The Q probability is
the easiest to define.

01:25:37.400 --> 01:25:39.170
It comes in very handy.

01:25:39.170 --> 01:25:41.670
But what I showed you
with the projection

01:25:41.670 --> 01:25:44.840
does not rigorously apply
to the Q distribution.

01:25:44.840 --> 01:25:48.500
It applies to the p
or w distribution.

01:25:48.500 --> 01:25:51.720
But the difference is, unless
you really go into subtleties,

01:25:51.720 --> 01:25:52.780
are minor.

01:25:52.780 --> 01:25:55.440
So intuitively, what
I did is correct.

01:25:55.440 --> 01:25:57.790
And to answer your
question, an eigenstate

01:25:57.790 --> 01:26:01.340
of the electric field, I have a
little bit problems with that.

01:26:01.340 --> 01:26:04.060
Because if you take this
projection, what you need

01:26:04.060 --> 01:26:07.450
is you need something
which is very, very narrow.

01:26:07.450 --> 01:26:10.930
But since this area is
in Heisenberg uncertainty

01:26:10.930 --> 01:26:15.880
limited area, it means delta
x delta p equals h bar over 2.

01:26:15.880 --> 01:26:18.490
The only way how you can
create this electric field

01:26:18.490 --> 01:26:21.020
is you can completely
squeeze it.

01:26:21.020 --> 01:26:24.540
So to the best of my knowledge,
an electric field eigenstate

01:26:24.540 --> 01:26:27.800
would be a completely
strongly squeezed state.

01:26:27.800 --> 01:26:29.830
We'll talk about that next week.

01:26:29.830 --> 01:26:31.690
But then you realize,
if you've completed

01:26:31.690 --> 01:26:36.650
squeezed your state
after a quarter period,

01:26:36.650 --> 01:26:42.560
this infinitely squeezed ellipse
is now standing upside down.

01:26:42.560 --> 01:26:45.090
And after a quarter
period your electric field

01:26:45.090 --> 01:26:46.860
is completely uncertain.

01:26:46.860 --> 01:26:49.520
So I think you can
define an operator,

01:26:49.520 --> 01:26:51.620
you can find a state
which has a sharp value

01:26:51.620 --> 01:26:54.320
of the electric field
at one moment of time.

01:26:54.320 --> 01:26:56.440
But then it rotates around.

01:26:56.440 --> 01:26:59.060
And what was a highly
certain electric field

01:26:59.060 --> 01:27:02.840
becomes highly uncertain later.

